Female. As in male except forewing length 9.45–11.2 , 10.24 + 0.61 mm (n= 10 ). Genitalia (
Figs. 42–43
): Papilla analis a curved elongate triangle, apex pointed; posterior apophysis approximately 0.83–0.88 X length of anterior apophysis; ductus bursae membranous, elongate; appendix bursae shorter than corpus bursae, with 3 coils; corpus bursae ovate; signa 4 scobinate bars.

Distribution (
Fig. 49
). Southern California east to Utah, Arizona, Colorado, New Mexico , western Kansas and Oklahoma, and scattered throughout Texas.
